org.fhnw.aigs.commons.communication

Class Message

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.fhnw.aigs.commons.communication.Message
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    BadInputMessage, ClientClosedMessage, ExceptionMessage, FieldChangedMessage, FieldClickFeedbackMessage, FieldClickMessage, ForceCloseMessage, GameEndsMessage, GameStartMessage, IdentificationMessage, IdentificationResponseMessage, JoinMessage, JoinResponseMessage, KeepAliveMessage, NotifyMessage, PlayerChangedMessage, ResultMessage

    public abstract class Message
extends java.lang.Object
    This is the base class for all custom Message classes. It provides an interface which will be used by the mechanisms behind the AIGS and AIGS BaseClient. Every message carries the information on who sent the message (in the case of a client-→server message) or who will receive the message (server-→client). Additionally every message carries the fully qualified name of the class, e.g. "org.fhnw.aigs.commons.JoinMessage" which allows the server or client to load the class.
    Every message can have as many additional attributes as necessary. They will automatically be translated into XML. The marshalling and unmarshalling is handled by JAXB.
    Please make sure that:
    • Every message class must have a default, zero-argument constructor!
    • Every message class must be annotated with the @XmlElementRoot attribute in the following way: @XmlRootElement(name="YourClassName")
    • Every field is set to private.
    • Every attribute that is not a primitive datatype MUST HAVE an empty zero-argument constructor.
    • Every field possesses a getter and setter which has EXACTLY this structure: get[CORRESPONDING ATTRIBUTE NAME], set[CORRESPONDINGATTRIBUTE] name. So the attribute isRed has a setter setIsRed and a getter getIsRed.
    • Every getter and setter is annotated with the @XmlElement annotation. The name attribute of the annotation is the name that will be used when marshalled to xml. If this has not been done JAXB will assume a name for the element.
    • Every array field must be annotated with the @XmlElementWrapper annotation. The name attribute of the annotation is the parent element's name, the @XmlElement's name attribute is the child's name in the marshalled XML form.

        public void send(java.net.Socket socket,
                 Player player)
        Sends a message to a player using a socket.
        Usually a call to Game.sendMessageToPlayer(org.fhnw.aigs.commons.communication.Message, org.fhnw.aigs.commons.Player) or Game.sendMessageToAllPlayers(org.fhnw.aigs.commons.communication.Message) would be the preferred method.

        Parameters:

      • parse_OLD

        public static <T extends Message> Message parse_OLD(java.io.StringReader reader,
                                                    java.lang.Class<T> messageClass)
        Turns a plain text xml message in a StringReader into a message object. Usually it should not be necessary to call this method as the messages will be parsed by the server and base clients already. However this method may be used to create custom xml-parsing implementations.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The desired class.
        Parameters:
        reader - A StringReader containing the message's text.
        messageClass - The desired class.
        Returns:
        The parsed message.
